# openrc-strip.list — v26 SLIM open-init strip manifest (v25 + stock web stack)
#
# Paths (rootfs-relative, NO leading slash) removed by openrc-assemble.sh from
# the unsquashed $FS BEFORE mksquashfs. Lines beginning with # and blank lines
# are ignored. `rm -rf` is tolerant of already-absent paths.
#
# Every path below was resolved against the br-0050 base-rootfs reference
# (/home/guillaume/.claude/jobs/5eb9adaf/tmp/base-rootfs) and ONLY listed if it
# EXISTS there. Each "verify-only-used-by" library was confirmed via a full
# DT_NEEDED reverse-dependency scan of the entire rootfs (needed-map.txt).
#
# DO-NOT-REMOVE invariant (must never appear here): libbwdpi.so libbwdpi_sql.so
# libsqlite3.so* libovpn.so libssl.so.1.1 libcrypto.so.1.1 /lib/modules/*/extra
# cfg80211.ko wl hostapd* nvram eapd wlceventd mcpd acsd2 wlconf ethswctl vlanctl
# fc/fcctl bcm_boot_launcher rc /rom/etc/rc3.d dropbearmulti sftp-server
# openrc-init* OpenRC libs.
#
# === v28 rc-removal investigation (RESULT: /sbin/rc is KEPT) =================
# The v28 task was to DROP /sbin/rc + its now-orphaned closed libs. A full
# DT_NEEDED reverse-dependency re-scan of the unsquashed keep-set established:
#   (1) ORPHAN SET FROM REMOVING rc = EMPTY. Every soname in rc's DT_NEEDED
#       closure (38 libs) is ALSO DT_NEEDED by at least one OTHER surviving,
#       non-stripped binary, so removing rc orphans ZERO closed libs:
#         - libbcm_flashutil/libbcm_boardctl/libbcm_util/libgen_util/libsys_util
#           -> DT_NEEDED by bcm_flasher + bcm_bootstate + tmctl (flash/boot tools,
#              KEEP). ★libbcm_flashutil is the NAND/pkgtb image writer — KEEP.★
#         - libwebapi/libovpn/libletsencrypt/libdisk/libbwdpi/libnt/libcodb/
#           libconn_diag/libamas-utils/libasc/libbcm/libwpa_client/libcfgmnt/
#           libnmpapi/libcurl/libjansson/liblldpctl -> DT_NEEDED by surviving
#           wps_pbcd and/or the AiMesh + notification daemons (asusdiscovery,
#           arpstorm, find_cap, cfg_client, cfg_reportstatus, nt_*, Notify_*).
#   (2) libbwdpi/libbwdpi_sql were NOT rc-exclusive (the "rc was its only
#       consumer" premise was WRONG): 7 surviving consumers remain after rc+httpd
#       go (wps_pbcd, asusdiscovery, arpstorm, find_cap, bwdpi_sqlite, libwebapi,
#       libbwdpi_sql) -> the no-op STUB STAYS; a full removal would dangle them.
#   (3) ★/sbin/hnd-write IS A SYMLINK -> rc★ (no standalone hnd-write binary).
#       The operator flash/recovery path (board/gt-be98/trial/trial-flash.sh:99
#       `hnd-write /tmp/trial.pkgtb`, which auto-commits the slot) runs THROUGH
#       rc. Removing /sbin/rc would break the trial flash + recovery channel.
#   CONCLUSION (conservative, "KEEP when unsure"): /sbin/rc stays; no lib is
#   added to this list for rc-removal. What v28 DID change: the VERIFIED-no-op
#   runtime rc invocations (`rc config_switch` / `rc config_extwan`) were removed
#   from init.d/net-lan + init.d/net-switch, so the open-init makes NO rc call at
#   boot (rc now survives ONLY as the hnd-write flash backend, never executed on
#   the boot path). A new DT_NEEDED integrity gate in openrc-assemble.sh fails the
#   build if any keep-set binary ends up with a dangling NEEDED lib.

