# === v26 STOCK ASUS WEB STACK (the open-OS serves :80 via /jffs/webui/webui) ==
# CONFIRMED LIVE-DEAD: :80 is served by /jffs/webui/webui (webui-go, its own
# /jffs/webui/www); the stock /usr/sbin/httpd is NOT running; nothing references
# rootfs /www at runtime; webui lives on /jffs (NOT in this rootfs). The stock
# ASUS UI tree + httpd are pure dead weight here.
#
# --- the ENTIRE stock ASUS UI tree (~34.0 MB raw) ---------------------------
# Includes the lang dicts (/www/*.dict), cgi-bin, SDN/aimesh/VPN/device-map/
# ajax/js/images/mobile templates — ALL stock-web data, removed with the tree.
www
#
# --- stock web server (the C httpd ASUS rc would launch on :80/:443) --------
# usr/sbin/httpds is a symlink -> httpd (the https variant); both go.
usr/sbin/httpd
usr/sbin/httpds
#
# --- web-EXCLUSIVE library back-ref scan (full-rootfs DT_NEEDED + dlopen) ----
# Candidate web libs in the base: ONLY usr/lib/libwebapi.so and lib/libdisk.so
# exist (no libwebui/libwebdav/cgi-helper libs ship). BOTH are KEPT — NOT listed:
#   libwebapi.so  DT_NEEDED by: /sbin/rc, /sbin/wps_pbcd, /usr/sbin/httpd.
#                 rc is in the KEEP-set (config_switch/sync_apgx_to_wlunit) and
#                 DT_NEEDED libwebapi -> removing it would break rc load. KEEP.
#   libdisk.so    DT_NEEDED by: /sbin/rc, /sbin/wps_pbcd + the (removed) lighttpd
#                 /webdav/samba cluster. rc DT_NEEDED it -> KEEP (rc must load).
# No dlopen-only referrers found (string scan == DT_NEEDED set). So NO web lib
# is stock-web-exclusive once rc is in the keep-set: none removed.

# === v29 UNWANTED ASUS-FEATURE DAEMONS (the #1 raw-MiB target, rc-independent) =
# Inventory roadmap target: the remaining OPEN bucket still ships ASUS feature
# daemons that the open-OS (single-AP wired/bridge+VLAN + WPA wifi + SSH + webui,
# NOT AiMesh) never needs. EACH path below was verified against the v28 keep-set
# (base-rootfs minus this list) on these two axes:
#   (a) NOT STARTED by the open-init: zero references in any board/.../openrc/
#       init.d/* service AND zero references in the graft /rom/etc/rc3.d scripts
#       (bcm-platform runs only S25..S50 = mount/nvram/drivers/ssl — none name
#       these). On the stock fw ASUS rc(PID1) launched them; rc is NOT PID1 here.
#   (b) STRIPPING DANGLES NOTHING for the keep-set: every entry is a LEAF binary
#       (or a dead symlink to an already-stripped target), NEVER a .so. Each is a
#       *consumer* of shared libs, not a provider, so removing it orphans no
#       keep-set NEEDED. ★libnt.so / libcurl / libcfgmnt / libwebapi / libdisk /
#       libsqlite3 / libwlcsm / libnvram / libshared etc. are KEPT★ (they remain
#       DT_NEEDED by rc + wlceventd + wps_pbcd, which are in the keep-set) — so
#       this strip frees ONLY the daemon-binary bytes, NOT any shared lib. The
#       v28 DT_NEEDED integrity gate (FATAL on any keep-set dangle) backstops this.
#
# FLAGGED — DELIBERATELY NOT STRIPPED (plausible user features / load-bearing):
#   wps_pbcd (WPS), miniupnpd (UPnP), avahi-daemon (mDNS), igmpproxy + udpxy + mcpd
#   (IGMP/multicast/IPTV), l2tpd + pptpd (VPN SERVERS the operator may host),
#   dnsmasq (the real DNS resolver/DHCP), eapd/wlceventd/acsd2 (wl glue — separate
#   decision), and the /sbin rc-applet symlinks (amas_lib/sw_devled/erp_monitor/
#   wpsaide/pc_block -> rc; tiny, dispatch through the KEPT rc).
#
# --- AiMesh control/discovery (single-AP, NOT AiMesh) -----------------------
usr/sbin/cfg_client
usr/sbin/cfg_reportstatus
