# === v30 RC REMOVAL — drop the closed `rc` binary + its now-orphaned lib ======
# The RUNTIME is already rc-free (v28 removed the no-op `rc config_*` calls from
# init.d/net-lan + net-switch; webui's sync_apgx_to_wlunit is open-init-guarded
# AND reimplemented open on feat/open-sync-apgx). `rc` survived ONLY as the flash
# backend via the /sbin/hnd-write symlink. With the OPEN flasher proven end-to-end
# (board/gt-be98/flash/open-flash.sh = dumpimage(host) + ubi-utils + CRC32-env
# metadata seq-writer + bcm_bootstate activate), hnd-write is no longer needed, so
# rc can be deleted outright.
#
# ★ORPHAN RE-SCAN (v30, from scratch — orphan-scan.py)★ Computed the closed libs
# orphaned when BOTH /sbin/rc AND /sbin/hnd-write are removed = DT_NEEDED-closure(rc)
# (37 sonames) MINUS the union DT_NEEDED-closure of EVERY OTHER surviving kept
# binary in the v29 keep-set (650 ELF files, 107 sonames). RESULT: exactly ONE
# closed lib is orphaned:
#   libconn_diag.so (82,644 B) — full-rootfs DT_NEEDED reverse-scan shows it is
#     referenced ONLY by: /sbin/rc, /usr/sbin/httpd (stripped v26),
#     /usr/sbin/asusdiscovery, /usr/sbin/arpstorm, /usr/sbin/find_cap (all three
#     stripped v29). No dlopen-string referrer beyond those same five. ALL five
#     are removed -> libconn_diag is fully orphaned. Its own NEEDED (libnvram/
#     libshared/libc) each have 100+ other consumers -> NO second-order orphan.
# Every OTHER soname in rc's closure stays ALIVE via a surviving consumer (notably
# wps_pbcd, kept: libamas-utils/libasc/libbcm/libcfgmnt/libnmpapi/libnt/libovpn/
# libwebapi/libwpa_client/libletsencrypt; and bwdpi_sqlite/hwinfo + libbwdpi stub:
# libbcm_flashutil/libbcm_boardctl/libbcm_util/libgen_util/libsys_util) — so they
# are NOT added here. ★libbcm_flashutil (NAND image writer) is KEPT — still
# DT_NEEDED by bwdpi_sqlite/hwinfo/libbwdpi.★
#
# KEPT for the open flasher / boot (NEVER listed here, all verified present):
#   bin/bcm_bootstate (standalone 9.7KB binary, NOT an rc symlink — activate step)
#   bin/ubiupdatevol bin/ubimkvol bin/ubirmvol bin/ubicrc32 bin/ubinfo bin/ubiformat
#   bin/ubiattach bin/ubidetach bin/ubiblock bin/ubinize bin/ubiscan bin/ubirename
#   bin/ubirsvol (+ usr/br/sbin/ubi* duplicates) — the volume recreate+write step.
#   sbin/bcm_flasher, libbcm_flashutil.so consumers — other flash/boot tooling.
#   wps_pbcd (WPS, shares rc's libs), wl/wlconf/hostapd*/eapd/wlceventd/mcpd/acsd2,
#   nvram, dropbearmulti, sftp-server, busybox, ethswctl/vlanctl/fcctl.
#
# ★v30+ MUST flash via the OPEN path★ — there is no hnd-write after this strip.
# board/gt-be98/trial/trial-flash.sh delegates to flash/open-flash.sh when
# hnd-write is absent (or GT_BE98_OPEN_FLASH=1). bcm_bootstate stays for activate.
#
# ORDER NOTE: the strip loop removes paths top-to-bottom and tolerates dangling
# symlinks ([ -L ] + rm -rf), so listing rc before hnd-write is fine — hnd-write
# becomes a dangling symlink after rc goes and is still matched + removed.
sbin/rc
sbin/hnd-write
usr/lib/libconn_diag.so
